documentation.text:
@title PremiumGenerator contract
 @author smeee
 This is a contract for lossless insurance premiums using Aave v2
Aave is used to generate interest for insurance applications
Beneficiaries deposit tokens into PremiumGenerator which deposit
them into Aave lending protocol
The interest earned is directed to the reserve associated with
the PremiumGenerator
Beneficiaries can claim their funds (and terminate their policy) at any time.
Functions deposit(), withdraw() and withdrawInterest() handle Aave interaction.*

@dev Allows a user to deposit funds for a specific validator index.
 @param _validatorIndex The index of the validator.

@dev Allows a user to withdraw funds for a specific validator index.
 @param _validatorIndex The index of the validator.

@dev Returns the address of the Aave lending pool.
 @return poolAddr The address of the lending pool.

@dev Returns the address of the Aave aToken associated with the WETH reserve.
 @return The address of the aToken.

@dev Returns the amount of unclaimed interest for the contract from the specified aToken.
 @return unclaimed The amount of unclaimed interest.

@dev Returns the balance of aToken held by the contract.
 @return The balance of aToken.

@dev Returns the normalized income of the reserve.
 @return The normalized income of the reserve.

@dev Returns the Aave liquidity index of the reserve.
 @return liquidityIndex The Aave liquidity index of the reserve.

devdoc.author: smeee This is a contract for lossless insurance premiums using Aave v2 Aave is used to generate interest for insurance applications Beneficiaries deposit tokens into PremiumGenerator which deposit them into Aave lending protocol The interest earned is directed to the reserve associated with the PremiumGenerator Beneficiaries can claim their funds (and terminate their policy) at any time. Functions deposit(), withdraw() and withdrawInterest() handle Aave interaction.*

_getATokenBalance(address).details: Returns the balance of aToken for the given aToken address.

params._aTokenAddress: The address of the aToken contract.

deposit(uint256).details: Allows a user to deposit funds for a specific validator index.

getATokenAddress().details: Returns the address of the Aave aToken associated with the WETH reserve.

getATokenBalance().details: Returns the balance of aToken held by the contract.

getAaveLiquidityIndex().details: Returns the Aave liquidity index of the reserve.

returns.liquidityIndex: The Aave liquidity index of the reserve.

getLendingPoolAddress().details: Returns the address of the Aave lending pool.

returns.poolAddr: The address of the lending pool.

returns._1: deposits amount of ETH/WETH deposited in contract
returns._2: premiumDeposit amount of ETH required for a deposit
returns._5: aTokenBalance Pool balance of aToken for the asset
returns._6: unclaimedInterest accrued interest that has not yet been claimed
returns._7: aTokenAddress address of Aave's aToken for asset

getReserveNormalizedIncome().details: Returns the normalized income of the reserve.

returns._0: The normalized income of the reserve.

getUnclaimedInterest().details: Returns the amount of unclaimed interest for the contract from the specified aToken.

returns._0: unclaimed The amount of unclaimed interest.

setReserve(address).details: Sets the reserve address.Only the multi-signature wallet is allowed to call this function.This function can only be called once to set the reserve address.

params._reserve: The address of the reserve contract.

withdraw(uint256).details: Allows a user to withdraw funds for a specific validator index.

withdrawInterest().details: Allows the contract to withdraw interest in the form of aTokens to the reserve.
